results.Title: Vince Lagana
results.Comments: This claim was a Malicious Damage claim caused by tenant. The real estate left as soon as myself and Vince arrived. Vince asked as many questions as he could but real estate rep not interested and just wanted to get away. As house was not lockable, Vince went ahead with assessment. Vince identified all malicious damage vs maintenance and tenant neglect. The report, quote and attachment submitted was very comprehensive. Vince even rung the claims dept to advise home not secure. Great job by Vince. No issues on this coaching session.

results.Title: Phillip Bell
results.Comments: This was a Quality Inspection. Phillip was very proactive with identifying issues with the painting of 1 wall. He called painter from site and arrange a time to meet with our insured. Phillip also advised insured timeframes. No issues with this coaching session. I found Phillip to be very helpful and informative towards our insured.

results.Title: steve mcclean
results.Comments:
claim declined lack of maintenance and poor roof pitch
car dirty from road works
id tag not used with customer business card provided
explained why not covered well and used photos to justify decision
went to incorrect address first before identifying correct house number
explained preferred builder procees and partnered lifetime warrenty

results.Title: Steve Mcclean
results.Comments:
1. Vehicle dirty from roadworks 
2. Id tag left at home no able to produce to customer 
3.Claim correctly identified and cash settlement warrented for part of the claim 
4. No cost provided for the cash settlement portion of the claim. Therefore claims do not know how much to discuss with customer 
5. Scope of work not provided however was discussed and option left for customers partner to contact estimator if any further questions required 

Overall good assessment and correct decision made estimator also went extra mile by measuring and checking adjacent rooms 
Unfortunate that cash settlement costs were not included in report

results.Title: Steve mcclean
results.Comments:
Overall very good assessment Steve engaged the customer identified thier needs and assisted them in relation to a discussion relating to extending the damaged awning. He explained the process well and made sure they understood they would be responsible for any work completed outside the scope of work. He explained he would arrange a specilist roofer to attend to quote and discuss their personal needs. 
Steve had forgotten his id tag earlier in the day and he called in to pick it up on the way to this job so he had it with him. 
The process at Dak Wal is that they do not provide a scope of work onsite they type it and send it via email or post to the customer therefore Steve did not provide this direct to the customer. He did however discuss the scope and made sure the customer understood what was going to occur. 
He also identifed old maintance issues that the customer understands they are responsible for. 
Thevehicle was still dirty from roadworks driven through the day before these assessments.

results.Title: Steve Mcclean
results.Comments:
Steve requested my attendance on these jobs as they were complicated landlord claims. Two claims were identifed and Steve asked many questions relating to how we work out these types of claims and how we aportion the damage to each claim. Steve had already inspected the property once and he had identifed the scope of work required. 
The property is also in very poor condition and he asked what we would treat as uninsurable, Maintenance , malicious damage and tenant damage. 
We also discussed the difference between ongoing damage done by tenants and malicious damage by tenants. 
Steve advised after this inspection he feels a lot more comfortable imn processing and deciding what to do on these types of claims.

results.Title: Glen Stalley
results.Comments: Excellent work by Glen. No issues

results.Title: Peter McIntyre
results.Comments: Coaching session performed on Peter as part of the Supervisor process. No issues with Peter's service. He has gone over and above for this insured to get him and his family back into the house from the caravan on site. Very well done by Peter.

results.Title: Rob from Men of Maintenance
results.Comments: Coaching done on Rob from Men of Maintenance due to targeting by Nathan Larkin. I found Rob to be very helpful towards our insured's issues. This was a large fire claim and the insured's were living out in the caravan and Rob repaired all the bedrooms first to get them back into the house. I also took our insured Mike aside who was very impressed with the work so far. No issues.

results.Title: Peter McIntyre
results.Comments: Coaching done for supervisor. No Issues.

results.Title: Alan McGrath
results.Comments: Alan performed estimate on repairs. No issues. Alan showed very good customer service skills. Also checked scope of works and report which is spot on. All costs F&R. Good work Alan.

results.Title: Alan McGrath
results.Comments: Estimate done by Alan. Insured very impressed with service. Checked report in OPUS which is F&R and accurate. Good work Alan. No issues.

results.Title: Daniel Bickerstaff
results.Comments: Daniel attended as supervisor. Also met trade on site. Daniel very good with customers. No issues with customer service. He also identified extra damage not picked up by estimator and advised OI process. Very proactive. No issues.

results.Title: Matt from Coastal Roofing
results.Comments: Matt from Coastal Roofing (Ensure trade) was very helpful and very good with OI's. Very disapointed Matt turned up in bright green boardshorts. This is not acceptable. No issues other than this. Called Matt Wilson from Ensure and advised we will not accept this tyoe of dress code. Matt will address this with his trade.

results.Title: Daniel Bickerstaff
results.Comments: Daniel was on site as supervisor. No issues. Very good service and OI very happy with the claim process.

results.Title: Baden Buchanan
results.Comments: Met with Baden who performed estimate. Real estate only spent 1 minute at then property and customer not there. Baden has identified all areas of concerns and was very good at recognising the maintainance related issues. No issues with Baden service, report and quote. Good work.

results.Title: Grant Marshall
results.Comments: Met with Grant who was estimating damage due to storm. OI's left key in external electrical box. OI's not home at time of inspection. I was not comfortable with OI's not being home. Grant performed his job well. Advised Matt Wilson tom advise his staff not to enter property if nobody home as they can blame us for anything that happens.

results.Title: Grant Marshall
results.Comments: Very good service by Grant. Good rapport with customer and recognised make safe needed to be done immediately. Great service by Grant.

results.Title: Baden Buchanan
results.Comments: No issues. Great service by Baden

results.Title: Steve Hartshorn
results.Comments: Met with Steve to who was performing QI. Steve has identfied area of poor plaster repair. OI did not want to get this fixed but Steve insisted due to the quality of work. Very good work by Steve to promote that the work was not the quality NRMA expect. Good work Steve.

results.Title: Steve Hartshorn
results.Comments: Met with Steve to perform QI on repairs. This customer was very angry and unhappy with the work done by Ensure's trade. Steve quickly got customer back on side and provided OI with a plan of attack to complete repairs quickly. This claim could have got out of control by Steve quickly put OI's mind at ease and provide a clear way forward. In the face of a difficult client, Steve did very well. Good work Steve.

results.Title: Darren Allen
results.Comments: Met with Darren from AJG on site. Performed estimate with real estate. Real estate explained what they wanted to claim and Darren very good at explaining what was and what was not covered and why. Good work.

results.Title: John Lettieri
results.Comments:
The mentee successfully explained the next steps of the process and outlined a proposed repair schedule that met the insureds needs. 
Explained excess payment options and applicable amount. 
Met the insureds expectations in arrnagimng for further make safe assistance to allow the insureds to enter/exit the damaged panel-lift door. 
The mentee failed to ask permission to take photographs and failed to provide further information regarding Lifetime Warranty offerred by NRMA and partner builder. Handed over the "Win the Customer" card with his business card -  no further explanation given. 
Overall, the mentee was professional and knowledgeable, and would have left the insured with a feeling of confidence with the insurance process.

results.Title: John Lettieri
results.Comments:
This was an assessment required following a concern identified from the customer regarding matching a second front facing roller door. Repairs to roller door x 1 and metal ramp for disabled son already completed and the insured was happy with the result. 
The mentee correctly and accurately explained the insurance company's matching materials guidelines, and provided a schedule and name of the trade to attend to complete the new works. 
Corrected the error with permission to take photographs identified in previous coaching example and applied to this claim. 
The insured expressed their satisfaction with the repair process to date, and with the further work needed.

results.Title: Ben Wilding
results.Comments:
Ben completed a detailed inspection of the damaged area and clearly and confidently explained how the repairs would be carried out to the customer. Ben provided a realistic time frames for the supply of the replacement door. Within an hour of the assessment Ben had made contact with the door supplier and had arranged a quote to be email in order for the report to be completed on his return to the office, Prior to the report being submitted Ben called the customer to discuss the replacement of the door and options for supply, as the insured has indicated they wanted an exact replacement to what had been damaged, 
The Lifetime warranty brochure was given to the customer at the completion of the assessment however the benefits of our prefer builders network were not explained nor discussed with the customer.
Ben also did not explained the next step in the claim in regards to  excess, next point of contact and repair process via AJ Grant. 
The above mentioned issues have been highlighted to Ben. 

It was also noted that this coaching session was Bens first day back from a 3 week holiday.

results.Title: Ben Wilding
results.Comments:
Assessment was completed without the customer onsite. 
Report submitted within hours of assessment message left for the customer to explain next steps findings etc 
Claim is to be cash settled as shared fencing and other damaged completed by the customer as a make safe

results.Title: Paul Daley
results.Comments:
There have been a series of improvement opertunities which have presented. 
Paul did not seam to have prepared for the inspection in that the incident was for a leaking vanity but when we attended insured advised that the showere may also be leaking. Paul did not inspect the vanity thoroughly and indicated that the shower will be checked for leaks by a plumber. This should have been a seperate claim, Paul did not ask permision to take photos, explain what repairs would be required, no contact details provided. Scope also missed the damage to the vanity as the insured had cut out a section from the bottem of the vanity to see where the water was tracking and Paul advised that that damage is explority work and not covered. While this is correct, the vanity had sustained other damage and I explained to Paul that the vanity carcas may still need to be replaced, including swollen shelves and doors. He had not noted the other damage and did not take any detail about the vanity. Customer asked who their contact would be and Paul said the office will be in touch

results.Title: Paul Daley
results.Comments: Paul forgot to ask permission to enter, take photos or to leave shoes on. Missed checking the ceiling space to confirm pipe repair or to check for damaged insulation. he noted some pre existing damage but missed other areas which were close by. Once again, did not provide a copy of the scope to insured, nor a business card and simply said if NRMA cover they claim they will contact and advise and then a scope and excess request will be sent out. Claim could have been varified by a visual inspection of the repaired pipe and customer could have been advised claim is authorised and ok to proceed once excess is paid. paul said old habbits die hard but some issues may pertain to AJ Grant office requirements. Otherwise paul was happy to receive feedback

results.Title: John Lettieri
results.Comments:
Tree impact claim - large areas of the back yard still covered with tree debris. 
The mentee took the correct steps in arranging for an immediate make safe of debris removal; appointing an arborist to advise on the safety of a large tree leaning and being supported by damaged concrete; and advising the insured that a second assessment will be required later in the week due to the extent of debris. 
Explained next steps in the process; contents cover and excess. 
Outlined all potential warranty related issues, touched upon Lifetime Warranty aspects and advised further information will be given at second assessment when area cleared. 
Customer satisfied with assessing experience.

results.Title: John Lettieri
results.Comments:
Damage to small floor tiles in the bathroom - the mentee correctly identified the cause as being tile growth/movement and poor adhesion. 
Explained to the insured how this occurs, and how this is outside of insurance cover scope. Provided an estimate of repair costs and scope when asked to by the insured. Appointing a specialist (plumber) to attend to confirm observations beyond doubt. 
Failed to advise who will be in contact once report submitted if not covered.
Has offerred JLG's services for a private quote if claim rejected.

results.Title: Blair Merchant
results.Comments:
Damage to rear awning due to strong winds; the mentee correctly identified reasons for damage and what the insureds needs to do to prevent future similar claims. Provided estimate and pointed out a nearby example of correct method of installation. 
Outlined all further actions required; provided details of specialist to be used for roof; schedule/timeframe advised; Lifetime benefits explained. 
The insured expressed their relief at the claim being readily accepted. No coaching issues with this observation.

results.Title: Blair Merchant
results.Comments:
Attended a JLG QA review with the mentee; the customer was advised of reason for attendance and was asked questions in relation to the claims experience similar to our NPS. Good repport established with the customer and their family. 
No coaching issues for this observation.

results.Title: Len Selems
results.Comments:
Len was empathic of the circumstances surrounding the theft and entertained the insured concerns. He provided comfort that the dowel being used was a good prevention method to stop someone from opening the window.
Len clearly explained process moving forward and lifetime warranty.

results.Title: Blair Merchant
results.Comments:
Attended QA review with mentee. He correctly identified workmanship issue with roof sheets (minor) which will be addressed to the insureds satisfaction this week. 
Established good connection with the insured early in review; QA questions in accordance with NPS. 
No issues with this coaching observation.

results.Title: Len Selems
results.Comments:
Len has attended the property to gather information in regards to newly raised concerns.Len displayed active listening stills to uncover the circumstances around dealings with claim in 2007.
Roofer was called whilst on site with the customer to arrange a suitable time.

Permission to entry the property and take photos was not gained and has been highlighted to Len

results.Title: Michael Boulton
results.Comments:
First landlord claim for mentee; no real effort made to engage the insured in conversation throighout the assessment. 
Scope provided was detailed and concise. 
The mentee provided an accurate and concise follow up to the insured regarding the next steps in the Landlord process. 
Further obervations required to accurately judge the mentee's attempts at building a connection with the customer in future claims.

results.Title: Len Selems
results.Comments:
Good customer interaction overall, Suggestions for improvement from earlier observations were implemented into this customer interaction. Great explanation of what was required in regards to repairs and how they would occur and time frame for completion.
No information was provided to the customer in regards to the excess.

results.Title: Vince Robinson
results.Comments: Overall a very good result. Claim was potentially under excess as the noticable damage was minor at this stage. Only real oportunity for development was that Vince did not indicate what would be covered if the became worse or if insured decided to proceed with repairs. Vince indicated that they do not write up a scope or discuss repairs rather indicating that as scope and report will be submitted to NRMA for consideration.

results.Title: Vince Robinson
results.Comments: Vince conducted a thorough inspection but dispite the claim being covered, did not advise the insured, nor provide a scope of works. I beleive this may be a system issues. As so far AJ Grant staff seem to be following the same proceedure.

results.Title: Vince Robinson
results.Comments:
Only minor damage noted to kick boards from leak. Client not willing to proceed due to a highe excess. Vince was very thorough with my only recommendations being that we could have re enforced the fact that NRMA does not cover the cost to locate or repair the leak and if the claim was to proceed and damage to the floating floor becomes evident, the the policy only covers the cost to the nearest doorway. 
A second observation is that AJ Grant do not provide a scope at the time of inspection but rather the customer is advised that if the claim is covered they will be sent a copy

results.Title: Darren Allan
results.Comments: Darren perfomed estimate. No resultant damage. Called Plumber from site. No issues. Great service.

results.Title: Darren Allan
results.Comments:
Darren performed estimate. This was a clear decline due to slab movement. Darren has taken lots of photos for complex assessor to make decision. 
No issues with service. Good job.

results.Title: Darren Allen
results.Comments: Darren performing estimate. OI did not turn up. Darren called OI from site and waited 30 minutes. No response from OI. Darren left business card in letter box and re called OI to advise he was leaving. Still no response from OI. Good service on phone.

results.Title: Jason Hoe
results.Comments: Attended site with Jason How to perform QI and check carpet issues. OI was noy happy with the restoration of carpet. Jason took it on himself and got a carpet supplier out to check carpet which was deteriorated under the pile. Jason very proactive on this claim. Great service

results.Title: Marcos Thompson
results.Comments: This was actually a post repair review in which the customer was complaining about the floor which was replaced and the fact that the edges of the floating floor were showing sign of lifting. Marcus conducted a very thorough review of teh area and advised the insured that he is of the opion that the product is faulty and would take full responsibilty of having it replaced

results.Title: Grant / Scott Harris
results.Comments: Grant and Scott conducted a very thorough inspectiong and clearly identified reason for the damage. Also noted that there are 2 sepearte incidents on the property. They identified that there is no listed event and that the damage to carpet is from rising damp and the damage to the ceiling is from condensation from the tin roof which does not have sarking. However, this was no explained to the customer that this is not covered. rather they said we righht a report back to PCR who then forward it to NRMA for consideration.

results.Title: Tod Coney
results.Comments:
The mentee met with the tenant at the insured property. No ID as yet as a new employee with JLG. Awaiting ID badge. Engaged in conversation with tenant easily and quickly. Sighted damage and explained works to be performed. Outlined next step in line with Complex assessors instructions. 
Did not seek permission for photos. 
Feedback given post observation. Further observations scheduled tomorrow.

results.Title: Blair Merchant
results.Comments:
Mentee attended property for the second time -  events and rapport already established. Examined damaged areas and provided opinion as to the cause. Outlined to the insured the possiblity of non-coverage for the loss. 
Explained next steps, and who will be following up process. Sought permision for photos and entry. 
No issues with this observation.

results.Title: Bryan Woodford
results.Comments:
-Did not request permission to enter or ask to take off shoes.
-Personal & freindly, good nature.
-More effort into W.T.C. methodology and more detail re the repair process etc. Training may assist.
-Feedback already provided to Bryan.
-S.O.W. inadequate. Door furniture identified at assessment as being able to be re-fitted. SPW allows replacement. not mentioned in report. 
-Discussion on site with custoemer to replace doors with temporary full panel doors & store leadlight glass, propert to undergo renovations.

results.Title: Bryan Woodford
results.Comments:
No duesl branded ID. 
Improvement from 1st previous coaching assessment where on this occassion Bryan asked to take shoes off and permission to enter, etc.
No resultant damage on this claim so mainly N/A answers. Bryan was thorough in assessment still.

results.Title: Bryan Woodford
results.Comments:
Denial well identified. Could have been more ascertive in the decision so I interjected and eventually confused matters. 
Good report & detail.
Certainly competant in identifying policy expectations for this nature claim.
Did not mention the low sum insured in the repaort. We discussed this pre assessment and it was discussed with Our Insured.

results.Title: Glenn Fitzgerald
results.Comments:
Engage with customer more with non technical assessment phase.
Very positive areas of improvement following initial coaching assessment.
Take active ownership of next phase of the repair process, i.e what to expect, excess collection, etc.
Potential 2nd incident and roof report not attached.

results.Title: Grant  / Scott Harris
results.Comments: Grant and Scott conducted a very thorough inspectiong and clearly identified reason for the damage. They clearly identified that the damage is due to a listed event but did not advise the customer the claim is covered. Rather they said we right a report back to PCR who then forward it to NRMA for consideration.

results.Title: Grant / Scott Harris
results.Comments:
Once again, Grant and Scott conducted a very thorough inspection, including accessing the ceiling space to view the water puipes to see if they are leaking. They clearly idendifed that the peipes do not run in the area of the dmage and could not be the cause. They also had a moisture reader and could tell the customer where all the water is. However, they thought it was up to the customer to identify the leak and have it repaired prior to any further work being done.
I explained that we should always have our builders organise a plumbers report which can identfy the leak and if required, repair the leak at the customers cost. None the less, the scope of works could still have been discussed with the insured so they know what would happen if the claim is accpeted and if it isnt.

results.Title: Tod Coney
results.Comments:
Mentee took on feedback from previous observations and asked permission for photographs; claim is GL in shower recess. 
Followed all necessary steps for the claim to proceed. 
No issues with this observation.

results.Title: Tod Coney
results.Comments:
Storm daamge to two storey home -  the mentee correctly identified specialist needed (roofer), and will have them carry out make safe today. 
Explained next steps, resultant damage. Roofer instructed to comment on roof as a whole, including the amouynt of tree debris blocking gutters, roof tiles. 
All measurements completed; good easy rapport and professional assessment with the insured. 
No issues during this observation.

results.Title: Peter Scash
results.Comments:
Difficult claim to assess and insured not present as only tenant with limited English. Difficult to get circumstances as impacted area in poor condition, many trees down which were not related to the incident and potential sub division. Peter is very thorough, clearly has an understanding of the policy and expectations of non compliant structures.
As discussed with Peter post BAR submission, the report suggests OI was on site which was not the case. Post assessment Peter spoke to OI and some of that conversation requires documenting in the report.

results.Title: Glen Stalley
results.Comments: Glen performed estimate for OI after break in. Whilst on site, Glen showed OI the website in which to choose a door. He also wrote out scope on site, he got police report and explained process in exact detail. I was very impressed with the excellent service Glen has given OI's and so were they. The service OI was given was very impressive and genuine.

results.Title: Steve Collins
results.Comments:
Steve needs to promote the benifbts of the prefeered suppliers scheme more. He needs to explain the lifetime warrenty and the link between NRMA and Dak Wal. 
Steve looked at a portable bathroom whilr repairs took place but did not think about the customers having 2 children in winter and the size of the house during repairs. I beleive temporary accomodatiomn would be more suitable. This was not discussed with the customer. 
Steve was not sure if we would cover the shower but as the entire bathroom will require water proofing this will be covered anyway.

results.Title: Steve collins
results.Comments:
Steve needs to promote the perferred partner scheme he did not explaine the link between Dak Wal and NRMA and did not explain the documentation as expected. He built up a good rapport with the customer and identified damaged areas that were not expected by the customer. 
He was not sure about coverage for a shower recess also affected and had to ask my opinion. The customers will require temporary accomodation however Steve only offered a portable bathroom although the house is very small and the customer has 2 children expected to o outside during winter and work in noise and building material.

results.Title: Steve collins
results.Comments: Steve took his time onsite but made 2 incorrect decisions relating to matching materials. He also offered a cash settlement for a floor without exploring other options to assist the customer. He also needs to promote the benifbts of the paterner performance scheme and the link between Dak wAL AND nrma. hE TOLD THE CUSTOMER about the lifetime warrently but di dnot explain it very well. Overall the claim was assessed ok but steve needed to explain detail further and ensure the customer understands the policy coverage and what we can do to assist within the confines of the policy.

results.Title: Steve collins
results.Comments: This claim was a reinspect as the customer was disputing a part refusal of 2 gates. I had to assist Steve explain why these may not be covered and I advised him to refer to claims as possible part refusal due to rusty gates

results.Title: Vincent Taylor
results.Comments: Vincent was well prepared, polite, friendly and professional. The customer was not on site and was represented by her cousin and brother. OI's brother entered the house approximately 15 minutes after the assessment began. OI's cousin showed Vincent the damaged areas and then left to begin cutting some timber as he is working on the house which is undergoing renovations. The claim does not appear to be covered and Vincent explained to OI's brother how he thinks the water is coming in (slab edge dampness) and that this is not covered however he also explained that a plumbing test will be conducted to confirm that there are no pipe leaks. I feel that an area of opportunity for Vincent would be to expand a bit more on who he works for and the relationship with SGIC. It would also be good if the coverage and who will be incontact should the claim not be covered were expanded on a little more to ensure OI knows exactly what the next steps will be. As there did not appear to be any real resultant damage apart from carpet, there was no necessity to write a comprehensive scope of works.This was a more difficult interaction as  OI was not there and OI's cousin and brother showed little interest in the proceedings.

results.Title: Nick Harris from Interline West Roofing
results.Comments: Met with (Trade) Nick Harris from Interline West Roofing during repairs. Repairs had almost finished. Whilst on site, Nick spoke to OI's re timeframe and small issues. He was very thorough and OI was happy with his response. No issues with this trademan.

results.Title: Richard Hutcheson
results.Comments: Met with Richard who was performing QI on mid repairs. Whilst on site, I took customer aside and ask him how he had found dealing with AJ Grant and their trades. He advised he was impressed and had no issues. Passed on feedback to Richard. Expressed to Richard he was doing a very good job with this claim.

results.Title: Carl Ellis
results.Comments: Met with Carl who was performing estimate from impact of tree. Carl very good with OI's and very caring about explaining to OI's who were elderly. Carl made sure OI's understood the way the process worked. Very good job done by Carl. Scope F&R. No issues.

results.Title: Glenn Fitzgerald
results.Comments:
-Engage with customer more.
-Win the customer methodoligy, doucmentation will come with better engagement.
-PPE equipment required.
-Take more time for assessment.
-If I was the customer I would not be confident of the next steps.
-Positively made the correct decision and decisive & confident there.
Overview photo poor.
-Roof report not detailed to mention foot traffic as discussed with plumber & estimator.
-No photos of adjacent roof elevation.
-Gutter lenths not identified.
Is the gutter related to this event or previous hail event?

results.Title: Jim Skinner
results.NameofPartner: Ensure Constructions and Restoration Pty Ltd
results.Comments: Coaching session was more for the purpose of providing Jim with guidance and advice for the new Landlord Malicous damage process. This was Jims first landlord claim and therefore the assessment was conducted together with both input from myself and Jim. Feedback and advice was provided at the end of this assessment which was then excuted on the second assessment which was also a malcious damage by tenant claim.

results.Title: Jim Skinner
results.NameofPartner: Ensure Constructions and Restoration Pty Ltd
results.Comments:
This was Jims second landlord assessment and a considerable amount of improvement was made in this observation fromt he first. Jim took into consideration feedback and advice which was given at APALB1404554, 
Jims Wrap up of the assessment was really affective as Jim was wrapping up he property he ran through all the damage mentioned by the customer and also ensured that he did not miss anything or there was no anything else the customer wanted to add. Jim also displays a very good technical knowledge for unlrealted issues he provided the customer with advice on what can be done and how to go about repairs which was much appreciated  by the customer

results.Title: Peter Scash
results.Comments:
It came across that Peter was accepting the claim but also arranging a roof report.
Could have set clearer expectations around the actual repair process, once excess paid .
Very Competent and takes sufficient time on even the smaller jobs.
Could have inspected adjoining rooms.
Eventual decision on BAR was "unsure" and considering the conclusion and first instance, the claim should be Accept.
No roof report attached.

results.Title: Peter Scash
results.Comments:
Parked in driveway. Jon has provided feedback.
Peter was in effect accepting claim but obtaining a roof report. 
In accepting the claim, explained well reasons for the roof report but did not explain the repair process, timeframes, excess collection. Did explain how the phsical ceiling repairs would be done.
Confident in Peter's attention to detail, manner, engagement and time on site.
Claims eventuall marked as unsure and without the roof report being attached it is difficult to determine correct decision.Should be either accept or do not accept, but not Unsure.
Maintenance mentioned for OI to engage an electrician to resecure a GPO when it is also allowed in the SOW.
Clearer dimensions required.

results.Title: Anthony Villani
results.Comments:
No ID and did not leave a business card. 
Engage more with the customer at the greeting stage and outline the process of the assessment.
Did not engage in the Win the Customer process.
Explain reasons for taking photos. 
Feedback provided.

results.Title: Alan McGrath
results.Comments: Attended site with Alan McGrath to perform estimate. OI school teacher and a little difficult to deal with. Alan explained process re decline or accept and appointed plumber to pressure immediately. OI not really happy about site visit but Alan did verything right dealing with this difficult and demanding customer. Good work Alan.

results.Title: Glen Stalley
results.Comments: Estimate performed by Glen. No resultant damage found. Glen very proactive in checking all rooms. No issues, very good assessment. Note: Glen and I attended this site twice as real estate did not turn up the first time and blamed us to OI. Rang OI to explain Glen was there even though real estate told OI he was not. OI Ok with this. GLen also very proactive and rung real estate before he left premises. Good Job.

results.Title: Alan McGrath
results.Comments: Attended property with Alan to perform estimate. Real estate did not turn up. Alan knocked on door and asked tenant if we could assess damage. Tenant was fine with this and very helpful. Alan immediately recognised the ceilings were in danger of collapse and tenant had a baby with her. Alan immediately rang trade to do make safe and batton up ceilings. I was very impressed with this action by Alan as it lept the tanant safe and the tenant was very appreciative of this action by NRMA and JL unlike real estate who did not bother to turn up. Alan also recognised this will be a decline on the basis of poor workmanship. Great job Alan.

results.Title: Richard Hutcheson
results.Comments: Met Richard on site to perform estimate on hail damage property. Richard was very impressive on site and won the customer. Richard perform his duties so well. I have done an estimate on his repairs and found them to be NOT F&R. called Richard and advised jobh well done but cost not F&R. Job will be tendered and more than likely lost.

results.Title: Sean Wilkinson
results.Comments: Performed inspection with Sean from JL on this old 2008 claim. OI claiming for mould and delamination. The delamination is due to Ensure poor work and the mould is due to atmospheric conditions. Sean clearly explained this to OI and advised report will be submitted quickly whjich it was. Good work by Sean, no issues.

results.Title: Josh Smith
results.Comments:
Josh attended the property with the details of the claim indicating a leaking laundry pipe had damaged the laundry tub. On enterring the property it was identified the customers plumber had ripped out the walls which appeared to be asbestoes. The broken fibro was all over the laundry. The customers did not seem to worry about the importance of the issue. 
The property was a family day care centre and the damage had been like this for 2 weeks. 
Josh advised the customers to close the door and not enter the room he arranged for the asbetoes to be removed while onsite and advised the customner someone would be onsite that day to arrange the containment. 
Due to this he was not able to measure the property or arrange a scope of works however he has arranged for the removalist to take pictures and measurnments . We are of the opinion the claim will be covered . Josh appeared flustered by what he had found and took some time to gather his thoughts in relation to the action he needed to undertake. He also asked about a hygenist due to the property being a day care centre which I advised should be undertaken.

results.Title: Josh Smith
results.Comments:
Josh attended the property after a fire. The customer was very old with health issues. The property is in poor condition and the kitchen was 1970 style kitchen. Under matching materials the customer is entitled to a complete new kitchen Josh did not pick this up. He also did not pick up the vynal floor damaged by the fire. 
Josh needs to revise the matching materials coverage and also needs to take a step back and identify all the needs of the customer including possible modifications to the kitchen etc to save costs that will benifibt the customer.

results.Title: Craig Cross
results.Comments:
Craig explained purpose of his visit and the fact that next steps will be contact from NRMA. Overall assessment went well 

Lifetime warranty and benefits brochure  given to the customer however report was to be marked unsure as Craig did not believe claim should be covered and if a decision was made to provide cover AJ Grant cannot warranty repairs. Do not believe warranty card should be given to the customers in this instance. believe that a more detailed conversation could have been had around the coverage and possible warranty issues with the insured.Craig clearly explained that fencing which  the insured wanted added to the claim would not be covered due to pre-existing condition. 

Its noted that Craig as only been with AJ Grant for 5 weeks.

results.Title: Craig Cross
results.Comments:
Customer was an elderly lady who had difficulties understanding the process and next steps, Craig offered to call the insured son and explain everything again which put the customer at ease.
Craig was very polite and helpful he offered to place the damaged gate in a safe area and also clearly explained that we would reuse this gate so that there was no issues with mismatching as damaged gate matched the fencing balustrade and front door and can no longer be manufactured.
Provided feedback in regards to seeking permission to take photos rather than telling the insured they would be taking photos.
Overall good customer interaction and tailored to suit the customer’s needs and situation.

results.Title: Garrick Moore
results.Comments: Garrick was engaging, polite, professional and well presented. Garrick explained everything clearly and built rapport with client. Garrick identified some deterioration noted to the roof sheeting on shed and roller door on UMR garage and Garrick advised OI that this would be in his report and submitted to SGIC or Garrick could discuss with me. We all discussed the deterioration and came to a resolution which enabled Garrick to confirm repairs with OI which was a good outcome. The only point that I have since discussed with Garrick is that the client  was advised that they would have to sign their scope and send it back however this is no longer a requirement.

results.Title: Daniel Bickerstaff
results.Comments: Met with Daniel who is supervising this claim. Ensure have painted ceilings and they have failed. Advised Kyle Brown of targeted audit as I belive Ensure will bill us for the first repair which has failed. Checked Asset and found variation not F&R. Also a reason for target. Daniel did very well with OI, no glaring issues other than he did not have ID card. Nathan Larkin informed.

results.Title: Garrick Moore
results.Comments: Garrick was very engaging, professional and friendly. During a recent meeting with Garrick, Chris and Vincent I provided them with a copy of the questions we use for coaching purposes so that they know the criteria. Part of this is the removal of shoes question and this does not appear to have been something Garrick has done in the past. I have given Garrick feedback in regards to advising OI straight away if claim is acceptable and confirming the SOW process and excess collection so that repairs can be started ASAP.

results.Title: Diego Santoro
results.Comments:
Mentee correctly identified 3 points of water entry to the home and advised the insured that these all sit outside insurance cover; provided evidence to the insured of maintenance issues; followed through with next step information for the insured; provided advice to the insured on how to make the home watertight. 
No issues with this observation.

results.Title: Diego Santoro
results.Comments:
Fire claim  - minor damage to laundry and cupboard. Mentee went on to the roof and provided details of roof void to the insured. Outlined scope, timeframe for repairs and next steps. Sold the insured on benefits of lifetime warranty. 
Professional assessment. 
No issues with this observation.

results.Title: Richard Hutcheson
results.Comments: Met with Richard who was performing estimate after impact from vehicle. Richard does not have a ID card. I have organised via Nathan Larkin. This was the only issue. Richard was very understanding and proactive when dealing with OI. I was very impressed with the way he dealt with this insd. Everything done right and how I would expect to be treated on a difficult claim like this. Great job Richard, keep it up.

results.Title: Garrick Moore
results.Comments:
Garrick thought on his feet and identified that damage to tiled area in the dining/kitchen was unusual and went into circumstances of a previous claim to attempt to ascertain cause of current damage. Garrick advised OI that there may be a pipe leak under the floor and that a plumber is required to identify any leak that may be present. 
Garrick was enthusiastic and engaging, polite and friendly. He confirmed that trades would be in contact to arrange a make safe to the tiled floor and what would be done to achieve this. Garrick outlined the steps that would be required to complete the repair.

A couple of points for consideration are 1) Would temporary accommodation be required given the tiled area is in the middle of the home and is used to access the bedrooms and the kitchen would be out of action? 2) I think OI could have been given a clearer indication of the outcomes should a pipe leak not be found and the subsequent policy coverage that may apply if no listed event found. I think OI went away with an expectation that it would be covered however that was not confirmed and a specialist (engineer possibly) may be required.

results.Title: Geoff Kempe
results.Comments:
Geoff was professional, well presented and courteous. 
Whilst on site Geoff was able to provide knowlegeable information for OI regarding the condition of gates and possible remedies for them. I think Geoff could have set a clearer expectation regarding time frames for rectification (Bali Hut) or at least an expectation of when someone from Key's would be contacting OI for an update. Geoff took responsibility for the work not finished off by the gate contractors and gave an undertaking to have the issues worked out. 

Geoff advised OI that he would need to do some research into who is able to repair Bali Huts and that he would need to get a price for this work as he has not had to do work to them previously.

There needs to be a sense of "can do" when approaching rectification works rather than being somewhat dismissive of some issues such as doubting the possibility of the Bali Hut having been damaged by the storm when the claim had already been accepted.

results.Title: Glenn Fitzgerald
results.Comments:
Difficult claim to pwn considering it is a damage by tenant claim; however when OI went straight into showing the damage Glenn could have interjected politely to get some history and fact. This is easier to do considering this assessment for a damage by tenant claim was with the customer. For example, was the property painted prior to new tenants occupation 2 years ago, etc.
Glenn wore jeans and Glenn has since confirmed that this is not acceptable attire. 
More customer engagement is required and ascertaining circumstances and this impacted many template questions.

results.Title: Anthony King
results.Comments:
This was Anthonys assessment on his own.
Anthony handed the life time warranty to the insured at the beginning of the inspection and said it explains the process "this is for warranty only"
 Anthiny when the insured was talking was looking at his book work which had the client then discussing the claim with me.
 For a first time effort Anthiny did well and with time and more inspections Anthony will work out his own way of dealing with the insureds.
Claim not covered on this cl;aim so no scope to be worked out.

results.Title: Michael Mc Call
results.Comments: Overall met Real Estate on site and assessment went very well. Explained refusal to agent and scoped and costed accordingly

results.Title: Michael Mc Call
results.Comments:
Customer was not onsite at time of inspection keys were picked up from NRMA office Taree. Michael called the customer from site and went over details with him. The house is in very poor condition and Micheal has identifed poor maintenance vs malicious damage. Although we believe the previous tenant may have been responsible we are not able to confirm this. 
This claim should be referred to UW as the property is in a very poor state.

results.Title: Michael Mc Call
results.Comments:
Michael called in to discuss additional damage identifed by the customer. While onsite he picked up the contract and explained the next steps . He also reviewed additional damage and identifed areas the customer had missed that had become aparant as the water had dried. The customer commented on how wonderful Michael had been and how his service has been second to none. The customer and her daughter were both grateful that we had sent such a good representive to attend to thier needs. 
Michael also went to the front villa as they are a strata title complex and he succsfully answerred the other owners questions and attended to thier needs

results.Title: Michael Mc Call
results.Comments: This claim was a reinspection as the customer disputed the roof of the property not being sealed. Michael explained this to the customer however the customer was still not happy. The customer looked to me as we had to advise the customer to contact NRMA as they did not take the word of the builder. I explained I was not from claims however past experiance indicates that what the builder advised was correct. Michael handled this claim well and did all expected of him under the curcumstances.

results.Title: Michael Mc Call
results.Comments: This claim was a basic bedroom claim where the damage to the bedroom was confirmed. The property is extremily well maintained and the customer is a builder. The customer advised he wants a cash settlement, as a result MIchael advised him he will need to provide a quote to NRMA and NRMA will decide on the most cost effective repair based on both quotes. HE also confirmed the scope of work with the customer and built up a very good rapport with him.

results.Title: Travis Purkis
results.Comments:
Attended with Mentee on QA assessment; identified issues with repairs; outlined timeframe and next actions for remediation with the insured. 
Apologised for workmanship and re-affirmed to the insured that the matter will be rectified. 
Professional observation. No issues.

results.Title: Travis Purkis
results.Comments: QA assessment with mentee. No issues during observation.

results.Title: Michael Mc call
results.Comments:
This property is part of 2 torrens title villas the customer has both for sale. Michaeal explained the cost of the claim as the customer requested if the claim was worth lodging. He explained the roof rails and the costs of these and explained that it is wroth claiming for the damage. 
The customer had just lost her sister hence the reason the villas are for sale and Michael was very empathetic towards her needs and how he explained the coverage.
